      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The economic argument hinges on the principle of fair competition within the domestic labor market. Unregulated immigration, particularly in low-skilled sectors, creates an artificial supply glut that drives down wages for native-born and legal resident workers. Strict enforcement ensures that labor markets operate under established rules, preventing wage suppression that disproportionately harms the working class. Therefore, border security is an economic policy that protects the earning potential and stability of the nation's citizens.",
      "source": "target",
